From 39b89c6788ed86d41e41939398ad6a032f1349a2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaradhana Sahu <quic_aarasahu@quicinc.com>
Date: Mon, 10 Feb 2025 16:46:36 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PROTOCOL:wpa_supplicant: Fix for max link association in
 MLD AP and station

When an MLD AP with n-links and an MLD station with n-links associate
over n-1 links, the station will continue to fetch the scanned BSS
even after association, as it is not associated over all n links.

In this scenario, there is no change in the RNR IE. Because of which
deauthentication frame will never gets triggered. This leads to n-1
link association instead of n-link association.

To fix this issue, remove the RNR IE condition and send the deauthentication
frame when all non associated links are present in BSS list otherwise it
scans until it find all non associated links in BSS list.

Signed-off-by: Aaradhana Sahu <quic_aarasahu@quicinc.com>
